From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guru Prasad Venkata Raghavan <vguruprasad91@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 13 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] metrics: emit OTel Gen AI KV cache semantic convention signals

Adds three Prometheus gauges that implement the OpenTelemetry Gen AI
semantic conventions for KV cache memory pressure (pending merge of
opentelemetry-specification/semantic-conventions#NNNN):

  gen_ai_server_kv_cache_eviction_rate          (evictions / s)
  gen_ai_server_kv_cache_allocation_velocity    (MB / s)
  gen_ai_server_scheduler_preemption_rate       (preemptions / s)

These are the three signals consumed by the memguard-cloud GBT OOM
classifier via the /v1/ingest/otlp endpoint.  The OTel Collector
filter/mkcp_signals processor selects only these three names so no
other vLLM Prometheus metrics are forwarded.

Feature is opt-in: set VLLM_OTEL_KV_METRICS_ENABLED=true before
starting vLLM.  When the env var is absent (the default), no new
objects are allocated and the code path is never entered — zero
overhead for the common case.

Rate computation lives in the new vllm/v1/metrics/kv_metrics.py
module so it can be unit-tested independently of the Prometheus
infrastructure.

OTel spec PR: opentelemetry-specification/semantic-conventions#NNNN
(update this before submission)

Base commit: 8d825b87d6590ca971823890f9705988b8709add
Apply check: git apply --check 0001-emit-otel-gen-ai-kv-cache-metrics.patch
